text: Yli-Ii is a former municipality in Northern Ostrobothnia, Finland. As of 31 December 2012, 2,179 people lived there. On 1 January 2013, the former municipalities of Haukipudas, Kiiminki, Oulunsalo and Yli-Ii merged to form the city of Oulu. It was founded in 1924.
